frameDefinitions: In this frame an Agent continues to possess a Theme for a Duration of time. ''
An Entity is understood to be experienceable within a particular set of delimited Circumstances, which may be more narrowly expressed by a Time, Place.
A Process of using or modifying is scheduled to be applied to a group or mass.
A Resource is depleted by some process, resulting in there being only a Remainder in existence some time into or after the process.
Despite some implication that a State would be interrupted, the Entity remains in the specified State.
A Self_mover responds to a (real or imagined) danger by moving away from it.
frameExamples: In her heart she must <t>retain</t> bitterness against those who had killed him.
This type of behavior <t>occurs</t> in several primate mating rituals.
Three more cars <t>remain</t> to be fixed.
There are only two poems <t>left</t> from Quayle
She had <t>fled</t> from DCS facilities several times before..
listRoleDefinitions: The person who has possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The entity which the <fen>Agent</fen> possesses for a <fen>Duration</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Agent</fen> has possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> keeps the <fen>Theme</fen>.
An object or event that is described as being available under delimited Conditions.
A temporal characterization of the circumstances of the existence of an <fen>Entity</fen>.
A spacial characterization of the <fex name=''>Circumstances</fex> of the existence of the <fex name=''>Entity</fex>.
A description of the state of the world in which the <fen>Entity</fen> can be experienced.
The activity that is being applied to the mass or the set of entities.
The mass or group that has not yet been processed.
The time when the <fen>Remainder</fen> is assessed.
The part of the Resource that the Process has not yet applied to.
The original set of items to which the Depletive_process applies one after the other.
The individual who owned the Resource that is being depleted.

A temporal setting or event which metonymically stands for the entities that were in existence then. The <fen>Remainder</fen> is part of the <fen>Original_context</fen>. This role occurs especially when abstract entities such as social institutions are seen as <fen>Resource</fen>s.
The Time when the amount of the Resource that is let is assessed.
A concrete or abstract <fen>Entity</fen>.
The <fen>State</fen> of an <fen>Entity</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>State</fen> is found to still persist.
The location where the <fen>Entity</fen> is in the <fen>State</fen>.
<fen>Self_mover</fen> is the living (or self-directed) being which moves under its own power.
<fen>Source</fen> is used for any expression which implies a definite starting-point of motion.
<fen>Path</fen> is used for any description of a trajectory of motion involving a landmark which is neither a <fen>Source</fen> nor a <fen>Goal</fen>.  This includes 'middle of path'' expressions.
<fen>Goal</fen> is used for any expression which tells where the <fen>Self_mover</fen> ends up as a result of the motion.
The direction that the <fen>Self_mover</fen> heads in during the motion.
The time when the motion occurs.

The <fen>Place</fen> is the location within which a defined motion takes place.  Any specified or implied  <fen>Source</fen>, <fen>Path</fen> or <fen>Goal</fen> should designate a location contained with the <fen>Place</fen>.
